# Docs & code clarity

Background: [knowledge/inbox/2026-07-18-docs-jsdoc-visibility.md](../../knowledge/inbox/2026-07-18-docs-jsdoc-visibility.md).
Product intent stays in `knowledge/`; developer-facing design lives with the code.

## Must

- Each `lib/<name>/` and `apps/<name>/` has a `README.md`: purpose, public API / entry points, structure, how to run tests/build. Link to `knowledge/` for intent.
- JSDoc on public surfaces: every `lib/` export, and each app's UI/logic entry functions. State what + why/constraints, not line-by-line narration.
- Visibility-first structure: split by responsibility so directory + file names reveal intent (extends separation-of-concerns). Prefer small focused modules over one large file.
- Update the README when the public API or structure changes.

## Must not

- Duplicate `knowledge/` intent verbatim into READMEs (link instead).
- Add redundant comments that restate the code (see making_code_changes).
- Grow a single file with mixed responsibilities to avoid creating a new module.
